            "name": "A dark gray medium-grained rock consisting of lightgray plagioclase grains, white to pinkish feldspar (plagioclase >> alkalifeldspar), green epidote or apatite, a black mafic phase and quartz. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.intermediate.solid.granod2.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "A purplish-gray, medium-grained granular rock composed of feldspar, a greenish to black mafic mineral and opaques. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.intermediate.solid.monzon1.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "This sample appears to be a black homogenous glass with good conchoidal fracture. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.intermediate.solid.obsidi1.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "A light gray medium-grained rock composed of pink feldspar, grayish plagioclase, quartz and biotite. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.intermediate.solid.qmonzo1.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "A dark gray fine-grained rock spotted with whitefeldspar grains in a dark gray groundmass with scattered mafics, opaques, and sulfides. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.intermediate.solid.syenit1.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "A medium-grained gray rock composed of whitish plagioclase, quartz, biotite, and a black mafic mineral. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.intermediate.solid.tonali1.spectrum.txt"
          },
          {
            "count": 1,
            "name": "The hand sample consists of very dark gray large tabular plagioclase with interstitial bluish-green granulated feldspar groundmass, with some opaque areas approx. 1-3 mm in size scattered through thesample. The Marcy anorthosite from which this sample was taken is described in: Buddington, A. F., 1938, Adirondack igneous rocks and theirmetamorphism: Geological Society of America Memoir No. 7, p. 19-33 and 258-259. Original ASTER Spectral Library name was jhu.becknic.rock.igneous.mafic.solid.anorth1.spectrum.txt"
          },
